So, Given Two Strings S1 and S2 of size N where different alphabets count in the string is same then only we can think of transformation.&lt;br&gt; we can match all characters from 1 to N-2
in both the strings in all cases.
Every time when we pick a character from first string, movement of that character can be &lt;br&gt;
```-2+1-2+1-2+1.............. ```&lt;br&gt;
We can move picked character to these places back in string&lt;br&gt;
```-2,-1,-3,-2,-4,-3....```&lt;br&gt;
After matching N-2 characters&lt;br&gt;
If last two characters were matched then we have transformed our string but they were not automatically matched then we can&#39;t do anything further.&lt;br&gt;
So the problem Problem lies with the last two characters we can&#39;t do anything with two character&#39;s movement.

For example&lt;br&gt;
*S1=abdc&lt;br&gt;
S2=abcd*&lt;br&gt;
we can&#39;t change *abdc* to *abcd* here because from *abdc* we can only go to 12 permutation out of 24 which are 			
*abdc, dabc, acbd, bdac, dcab, bacd, adcb, bcda, dbca, cbad, cadb, cdba*&lt;br&gt;

**Optimally Fast answer By counting inversions** &lt;br&gt;

